### SECTION 3 — TWA IMPLEMENTATION PLAN

**3.1 TWA Tool Recommendation**
Two options — recommend one based on the project setup:

| | Bubblewrap (Google CLI) | PWABuilder (Microsoft web tool) |
|-|------------------------|--------------------------------|
| Requires | Android Studio + Java | Just a browser + deployed URL |
| Output | Full Android Studio project | Ready APK/AAB download |
| Customization | Full | Limited |
| Best for | Teams with Android experience | Teams without Android experience |

Which is right for this project and why?

**3.2 Technical Requirements Checklist**
List every requirement TWA has and whether TechNova currently meets it:

| Requirement | Required value | Current status | Action needed |
|-------------|---------------|----------------|---------------|
| HTTPS | Must have valid SSL | | |
| Service worker | Must exist and be active | | |
| Web manifest | Must have 192px + 512px icons | | |
| start_url | Must be / | | |
| Lighthouse PWA score | Must be ≥ 80 | Unknown — run Lighthouse | |
| assetlinks.json | Must be served at /.well-known/assetlinks.json | | |

**3.3 Digital Asset Links (assetlinks.json) Plan**
This is the most critical TWA requirement. Plan exactly how it will be implemented:

- Where will the file be served from? (Express route on backend, or static file in public/)
- What information is needed to generate it? (list each piece of data)
- When can it be generated? (what must happen first)
- How will it be verified after deployment?

**3.4 TWA Configuration Values**
Based on the codebase, propose values for every TWA config field:

```
packageId:          com.[company].[appname]  (derive from codebase)
appName:            [from codebase]
launcherName:       [max 12 chars]
startUrl:           /
themeColor:         [from tailwind.config.js brand color]
backgroundColor:    [from tailwind.config.js]
iconUrl:            [path to 512x512 icon]
display:            standalone
orientation:        portrait
enableNotifications: true
```

**3.5 Signing Keystore Plan**
- What command generates the keystore
- What values to use (alias, organization name)
- Where to store it (must NOT be in git)
- What happens if it is lost (explain the consequence clearly)
- Whether to use Google Play App Signing (recommended — explain why)

